                  <span class="c00">&gt; <i>WinAmp came out in 1997, 2.x was released in 1998. Real time streaming media.</i><p>Related to GP&#x27;s &quot;Software was a lot less capable back then.&quot; - somehow, WinAmp 2.x seems to be peak capability of music players; I don&#x27;t recall any player made later that would be comparable in features for playing local music (with maybe the exception of Foobar2000).<p>My rose-tinted glasses have some scratches on them, but I still maintain that software of today didn&#x27;t gain many meaningful features over the late 90s &#x2F; early 2000s, and yet it grown tremendously in size and resource use.<span>
