                  <span class="c00">I think the bottleneck in the 90s was not software, but hardware. Most of the software was almost as capable and arguably more efficient than the software made _today_<p>The most efficient software today is still built with the lower level mindset of conserving memory and increasing runtime performance (Browsers, Compilers, Vector Graphics, Games etc)<span>
