                  <span class="c00">...why not sublime?<p>I don&#x27;t understand why these electron editors are popular at all. With all due respect to the people working on them (because it really isn&#x27;t their fault for the most part), they&#x27;re bloated slow pieces of shit. I don&#x27;t like electron in general, but its an especially bad choice for a text editor intended for developers.<p>If you don&#x27;t like vim or emacs, sublime does what the electron editors do but better. Its probably the most performant of all the text editors I&#x27;ve used; vim and emacs both don&#x27;t like gigantic logfiles, but sublime handles them without issue. The only bad things I can say about it are lacking vim emulation and worse dev experience than Emacs. But then again, I&#x27;ve never used an editor anywhere near as nice as Emacs in terms of language integration for a lot of the languages I work with.<span>
