                  <span class="c00">Im probably super out of the loop but I always wonder about these kind of comments. Even if electron uses say 500% more resources than vim, why in the world would that matter beyond personal irritation for anyone making 6 figs doing software development? I get the impression from these arguments that people are trying to do serious software development on 5 year old budget hardware. In any profession, investing in your tools is par for the course. Most of the geeks I know have far more machine than they could ever use as a matter of pride. Why would a few hundred extra megs of ram or a few more clock cycles matter if you have gigs of ram at your disposal and many cores? If the tool is good and doesn&#x27;t touch your limits why does it matter if it&#x27;s as slim as a demoscene release or as hungry as a browser tab? No judgement, genuinely curious.<span>
